 <span style="font-size: 12px"><span style="color: rgb(0,0,0)">The web part&nbsp;provides a way&nbsp;to create a&nbsp;password reset&nbsp;page with a custom&nbsp;design that&nbsp;can be used instead of the&nbsp;default system page.&nbsp;The URL of such a page must be entered into the <strong>Reset password page</strong> setting in&nbsp;<strong>Site Manager -&gt; Settings -&gt; Security &amp; Membership -&gt; Passwords</strong> or into the <strong>Reset password page URL</strong> property of individual <strong>Logon form</strong> web parts.<strong> </strong>Once assigned, the links in the confirmation e-mails sent as a reply to password reset requests will lead to the page. There, the web part will automatically process the query string parameter and allow users with valid requests to change their password.</span></span></p>', 'b8587464-1bd5-46fd-be4a-a7e611ed70eb', '20120814 08:58:49', 0, 0, N'<form></form>', NULL, NULL, NULL, '895ee185-e37b-4b15-9876-af3cbebe34c9')
